.TH "dynevent_arg_add" 9 "dynevent_arg_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dynevent_arg_add \- Add an arg to a dynevent_cmd
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dynevent_arg_add
.BI "(struct dynevent_cmd *cmd "  ","
.BI "struct dynevent_arg *arg "  ","
.BI "dynevent_check_arg_fn_t check_arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cmd" 12
A pointer to the dynevent_cmd struct representing the new event cmd
.IP "arg" 12
The argument to append to the current cmd
.IP "check_arg" 12
An (optional) pointer to a function checking arg sanity
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Append an argument to a dynevent_cmd.  The argument string will be
appended to the current cmd string, followed by a separator, if
applicable.  Before the argument is added, the \fIcheck_arg\fP function,
if present, will be used to check the sanity of the current arg
string.

The cmd string and separator should be set using the
\fBdynevent_arg_init\fP before any arguments are added using this
function.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if successful, error otherwise.
